<br>
When loot becomes more important than roleplay;<br>
<br>
When the main attraction for the server is its special non-no-drop rules as opposed to roleplay preferred;<br>
<br>
When people behave as rudely (Or WORSE) than on regular &quot;bluebie&quot; or &quot;carebear&quot; servers;<br>
<br>
When roleplay takes a back seat to pretty much everything else on a &quot;roleplay preferred&quot; server...<br>
<br>
Then yes, I would have to say that the Golden Age of Firiona Vie is indeed over.<br>
<br>
The patches were not the cause.  They were the catalysts and good indicators of the direction.  The symptoms were evident in the d00d to rp'er ratio when the ruleset was modified in order to keep the server population up (or so we were told).<br>
<br>
I cry for Firiona Vie.<br>
<br>
But who the fuck am I?  I'm no powergamer. I'm no Uber-Looter.<br>
<br>
I'm just a roleplayer, and not a very good one at that.<br>
<br>
But Firiona Vie was my home.<br>
<br>
Poor, polluted Server.<br>
