<br>
I started on FV, cause the Rollplaying perfered caught my eye. I thought, that seems like me. <br>
<br>
I've created other characters on other servers for fun, but mainly play on FV. You could say it's 95% FV, 5% other servers. It's well over a year.<br>
<br>
For me, the server has changed much. First, it is more crowded. But not nearly as bad as other servers. FV at first seemed a haven for those that didn't like PvP or the regular Blue servers with it's long time players.<br>
<br>
The idea behind nothing being no drop and TLC seemed geared towards people HAVING to work together to complete quests. When I was the newbiest of all newbies, running around EC trying to get my armor quests done. People would just give you things you needed. And on that level, they still do for the most part. Now and then you run into the person that wants 10plat for a jar of snake bile. I even had a level 30 player give me 17 plat for simply being nice to him. I never begged for anything. I got some really lucky breaks in my lower levels. And in return I tried to give other lower levels breaks. For many season, I would give decent weapons and items that weren't worth trying to sell to lowbies. I would make a game of wandering around EC and the first person to find me got the item.<br>
<br>
I really don't see that as much now. For me the bazaar changed alot. Suddenly it seemed like everything was viewed with a $ in some peoples eyes. If I can sell it, I will. <br>
<br>
More dOOds as people like to call them have shown up on the server. Drawn because of the fact of being able to sell everything. These are the people you read about camping and running all over other players in the Soapbox. Those that move into a camp and say and do anything to try and get you to leave. I've encountered many like that in the last few months. Most I just ignore and go about my business. Then even more dOOds came once it was found out you can bypass TLC with the raid feature. <br>
<br>
But yeah, FV has changed. I can't say for good or bad. Because everything changes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eliezeroferudin>Eliezer of Erudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Order of Crimson Hands</span><br>  Posts: 1417<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/21/03 9:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=37.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: FV lost</span><hr size=1> EQ was never an ideal platform for Roleplaying, changes in the game and the nature of the high-end also tends to discourage RP in some ways.<br>
