Find me a genuine temper tantrum or personal attack (other than my point, which is that they are being selfish). Stating my opinion about his opinion and attitude is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>not</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> a personal attack, i'm sorry. As far as the 'lumped into any grouping that claimed him,' please explain to me what you mean by this, because it sounds... inflammatory.<br>
<br>
I refuted his points, sure I was mean about it, but so what? I'm not mean spirited, i'm just offended enough at his and Tzaroth's means of expressing them that I am furious.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If you are going to argue/debate then do so, but man telling people to stop whining while you are laying on the ground kicking and screaming and calling names...that is just ridiculous.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Once again, you are accusing me of something I didn't, in my opinion, do. Please outline for me the 'name calling' I am engaged in. And I have argued this, for months. I still hold the same view point now as I did then: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The people who moan about the May 8 2002 changes are being selfish.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> It does not bother me that they are being selfish, it bothers me that they claim that it has ruined the server. The implication is that people who don't agree with them have ruined the server and this is frankly belittling, insulting, degrading and so infuriatingly self-righteous as to inspire me to verbal violence.<br>
<br>
If you don't like that I'm mad, oh well. So sorry.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I shouldn't bother saying this though, he will be defended because many of the 'higher' powers here agree with his point and will overlook the personal attacks and senseless belligerence. Things that are supposed to be no nos even in this forum.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Thank <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>you</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Fajon for insulting me. I am quite the opposite of senseless and frankly I don't care what the 'higher powers' think of me. I do not supplicate to them for protection, I do not ask them for wisdom unless it is on an administrative issue and I certainly do not consult them before or after I post. As far as them agreeing with me, well so what? They have a right to agree or disagree as they choose, however I counter your accusation (and it is an accusation) with this:<br>
<br>
Why do you care? Is it because you believe that you can drown out my very valid point with volume? Do you wish this to become a shouting match?<br>
<br>
It seems that the May 8'ers all seem to think that they can generate enough noise to break the patch. Here's a novel way to look at it. Our complaints got the May 8 patch roughly 6 months into the server life. You've had more than a year since then and still haven't gotten it reversed. Consider how many active voices on this server were clamoring on each side now, given that time discrepancy.<br>
<br>
Now, not only do I think that the May 8 2002 patch was the best thing for the server, I also think that my viewpoint is actually in the majority. That being said, Do you think that it is fair for you or them to claim things would be better if a minority imposed a restrictive set of rules on the majority? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Nakath Thunderbush<br>
